  <article title="Hepatitis A">
       <p class="intro">
                  Hepatitis A is a contagious liver disease that usually spreads through food or water contaminated with the hepatitis A virus or close personal contact with an infected person. In 2018, multiple states reported outbreaks, primarily among people who use injection and non-injection drugs, homeless individuals, and their close direct contacts.
              </p>    
  
